-- Russia to Spend 3.7 Trillion Rubles on Coal Industry by 2030
-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 2012-01-24T07:59:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/russia-to-spend-3-7-trillion-rubles-on-coal-industry-by-2030-1-.html
Russia will spend 3.7 trillion
rubles ($120 billion) on the coal industry through 2030, Prime
Minister  Vladimir Putin  said today in Kemerovo, Siberia.  The government will allocate more than 5 billion rubles on
restructuring the industry in 2012, Putin said at a meeting on
the industry. Russian companies produced 336 million tons of
coal in 2011 and may reach 430 million tons by 2030, Putin said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
 iarkhipov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
